post_text:
July 30, 2020

After much thought and consideration of all contributing factors, it is with a heavy heart that Unity Point School has decided to cancel all fall sports seasons for the 2020-2021 school year.

We realize the disappointment created by this decision for our students and families but would hope there is an understanding in our efforts to maintain the health and well-being of our school community as our top priority during these unprecedented times.

We will reevaluate the situation as the basketball and cheer seasons approach in October and provide a decision at that time.

Should you have any questions, please contact Dr. Lori James-Gross at 618.529.4151.

Unity Point Parents & Community:

STRONG BEGINNINGS...PART 2

The following URL provides information regarding the district-wide academic start to the 2020-2021 school year.

URL: https://bit.ly/strongbeginnings

The first day of student REMOTE attendance will be Monday, August 17 and will continue through Friday, September 11. At that time, we will reassess the status of COVID-19 and determine if our approach to learning needs to be modified.

Please review the information and feel free to contact Dr. Lori James-Gross, Superintendent, at 618.529.4151 with any questions or concerns.

As we look to provide a healthy and safe environment under these circumstances, we intend to continue to provide a strong academic and whole child experience that is synonymous with Unity Point.

Please check out the "I Am a Rural Teacher" (IAART) profile of our very own Leslie Varble via the link below.

If you're unfamiliar with IAART it is "a national advocacy campaign that gives voice to rural teachers. The program is a collaboration between the Rural Schools Collaborative, National Rural Education Association, Community Foundation of the Ozarks, Ozarks Teacher Corps, and The University of West Alabama’s Black Belt Teacher Corps. The “I Am a Rural Teacher” campaign is made possible by a grant from The Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation.

https://iamaruralteacher.org/profiles/leslie-varble-carbondale-il

post_text: The Trojan Tribe is celebrating Teacher Appreciation Week and we need your help! Take some time this week and draw your teacher a picture showing your appreciation for them. Then either take a picture of it and email it to them or turn it in with your learning packet so they will get to see it. Thank you!
